To create a chessboard in LaTeX using FEN notation, we can use the `chessboard` package. Here's an example:

1. First, include the `chessboard` package in your LaTeX document preamble:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
```

2. Then, in your document body, you can use the `\chessboard` command to display the board. For example, let's say you have the FEN notation `rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1` that represents a starting position. To display this board, you can use:

```latex
\begin{document}
\begin{chessboard} [setfen={rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR}, color=white]
 \end{chessboard}
\end{document}
```

This will display the chessboard with the starting position in white's perspective. You can change the color to black by adding `color=black` in the `[setfen={...}, color=...]` options. Note that the `[setfen={...}]` option is used to set the starting position using FEN notation.

Also, you can use other options like `fontsize`, `showmover`, and `boardlabel` to customize the chessboard. For more information, you can refer to the documentation of the `chessboard` package.

